============================================================
Comparison with ViT-L results:
                ViT-L    ViT-B    Gap
  VQA v2 Acc:   74.8     72.1    -2.7
  MSCOCO Acc:   73.5     70.8    -2.7
  RefCOCO F1:   67.2     58.9    -8.3
  SNLI-VE Acc:  78.1     75.2    -2.9

Notes:
  - VQA, MSCOCO, and SNLI-VE show modest drops (2.7-2.9 pts)
    with ViT-B, which is expected given the smaller backbone.
  - RefCOCO shows a notably larger gap (8.3 pts in F1).
    This is likely because RefCOCO requires fine-grained
    spatial understanding, and ViT-B has lower spatial
    resolution in its feature maps compared to ViT-L.
  - Hyperparameters were properly tuned for ViT-B
    (unlike the earlier pilot run which used ViT-L params).

